[[File:WookieeSeason.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''"Wookiee Season"'']]
'''JAKe''' is a UK graphic artist and designer. Although his work has appeared on record sleeves, posters, as toys, and in animated form, his work for [[Lucasfilm]] has mainly been for merchandise, for both the ''[[Star Wars]]'' and ''[[Indiana Jones]]'' franchises. He has three Star Wars books published by Chronicle - ''[[How to Speak Wookiee: A Manual for Intergalactic Communication]]'', ''[[How to Speak Droid with R2-D2: A Communication Manual]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: How to Speak Astromech with BB-8]]''. JAKe is also the creator and director of Geekboy, a series of animated shorts which appeared on the Sci Fi channel, in which the title character meets notable science fiction icons including [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]].

JAKe appeared at the [[Celebration IV]] and [[Celebration Europe (2007)|Celebration Europe]] art shows.

